===iTunes releases===
The first series of ''Mrs. Brown's Boys'' has been available on [[iTunes]] since 31 October 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://itunes.apple.com/gb/tv-season/mrs.-browns-boys-series-1/id462277155|title=Mrs. Brown's Boys, Series 1HD|publisher=http://itunes.apple.com |date=N/A |accessdate=9 May 2012}}</ref>

==Spin-offs==

===Film===
There have been reports that an estimated <U+00A3>3.6m deal is in place with [[Universal Studios]] to start production on the film version of the series. A spokesman for O'Carroll has also confirmed that the film will have a distinctly Dublin flavour, "It's Dublin humour so you're going to need Dublin actors and technicians to get it right for the big screen."<ref>{{cite web|title=Mrs Brown's Boys gets a $6m movie deal|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/film-tv/news/mrs-browns-boys-gets-a-6m-movie-deal-16212911.html|publisher=Belfast Telegraph|accessdate=22 September 2012}}</ref> Despite funding being secured, O'Carroll confirmed that the script has not been written. "I haven't written it yet. That's what success does, they give you money and say 'Whatever you think'. So I've taken the money!".<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/2012/0529/mrsbrownsboys.html | work=RT<U+00C9> News | title=Mrs Browns Boys to be made into movie | date=29 May 2012}}</ref> At the 2013 National Television Awards O'Carroll confirmed the film had been written and will begin shooting the following autumn.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brendan O'Carroll confirms 'Mrs Brown' movie at NTAs 2013 |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a453373/brendan-ocarroll-confirms-mrs-brown-movie-at-ntas-2013.html|accessdate=27 January 2013}}</ref>

Filming is due to start in [[Dublin]] in September 2013 under the working title, ''Mrs Brown D'Movie''.<ref>{{cite web|title=<U+00A3>3.6m budget for Mrs Brown's movie|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/news/2012/09/19/16168/%A33.6m_budget_for_mrs_browns_movie|publisher=Chortle|accessdate=22 September 2012}}</ref>

===Game show===
O'Carroll has also confirmed that a game show starring Mrs Brown is in development with production company [[12 Yard]]. A non-broadcast pilot is expected to be recorded in late 2012. A full series is also due to be broadcast in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last=Khalsa |first=Balihar |url=http://www.broadcastnow.co.uk/news/commissioning/mrs-brown-gets-saturday-night-gameshow/5045334.article |title=Mrs Brown gets Saturday night gameshow &#124; News &#124; Broadcast |publisher=Broadcastnow.co.uk |date=2012-08-14 |accessdate=2012-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Exciting New Pilot!|url=http://www.12yard.com/2012/08/13/exciting-new-pilot/|publisher=12 Yard Productions|accessdate=22 September 2012}}</ref>

===Animated series===
O'Carroll has also confirmed that an animated version of the show is in development.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comedy.co.uk/news/story/00000771/bbc_pilot_brendan_ocarroll_mrs_browns_boys_cartoon/ |title=New pilot and Mrs. Brown's Boys cartoon in production - News - British Comedy Guide |publisher=Comedy.co.uk |date=2012-03-06 |accessdate=2012-09-30}}</ref>

